'''Norman Harold Heath''' (31 January 1924 &ndash; November 1983) was an English [[association football|football]]er who played as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]].

== Biography ==
Heath was born in [[Wolverhampton]]. He joined [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] as an amateur in May 1942 and turned professional in October 1943, having made his debut in September 1943 in the [[Football League North]] against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]. He died in [[Great Barr]], [[Birmingham]] in November 1983.

